<h1 id="create-a-purchase-order-governed-by-budget">Create a purchase order governed by budget</h1>


<p>Use this procedure to create a purchase order that is checked for available budget. This recording uses the USMF demo data company.</p>
<h2 id="review-the-budget-control-configuration">Review the budget control configuration</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Budgeting &gt; Setup &gt; Budget control &gt; Budget control configuration.</li>
<li>Click the Budget funds available tab.</li>
<li>Click the Documents and journals tab.</li>
<li>Click the Define budget control rules tab.</li>
<li>Click the Define budget groups tab.</li>
<li>Close the page.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="create-the-purchase-order-header">Create the purchase order header</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Procurement and sourcing &gt; Purchase orders &gt; All purchase orders.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Vendor account field, enter or select a value.</li>
<li>Expand the General section.</li>
<li>In the Accounting date field, set the date to '2016-01-01'.</li>
<li>Click OK.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="add-a-purchase-order-line">Add a purchase order line</h2>
<ol>
<li>In the Procurement category field, enter or select a value.</li>
<li>Set Quantity to '2'.</li>
<li>In the Unit field, enter or select a value.</li>
<li>Set Unit price to '10000'.</li>
<li>Click Financials.</li>
<li>Click Distribute amounts.</li>
<li>In the Ledger account field, specify the value '601300-001-023--'.</li>
<li>Close the page.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="perform-budget-checking">Perform budget checking</h2>
<ol>
<li>Click Financials.</li>
<li>Click Perform budget checking.</li>
<li>Click Financials.</li>
<li>Click Budget check errors or warnings.</li>
<li>Click Close.</li>
</ol>
